    "attributes": {
        "action": "Provide all small companies not entitled to existing support a grant of \u00a325,000",
        "additional_details": "Just when small companies need urgent support during the current Covid19 pandemic & lockdown many have been excluded by ridiculous government set eligibility criteria from:\r\n \r\n1. \u00a310,000 cash rate grants\r\n2. \u00a315,000 (6 months x \u00a32,500) furlough employee support grants\r\n3. Covid19 business interruption loans scheme\r\n \r\nSo the government as a minimum must urgently offer small micro UK Limited companies that have corporation tax filing history but are not entitled to existing schemes with cash grants of \u00a325,000.",
        "background": "Provide all small companies that have corporation tax filing history but have not been able to access the \u00a310,000 rate grant or the 6-months furloughed employee support of \u00a315,000 a cash grant of \u00a325,000.",
